course.subject: PSYCH
course.course_title: Introduction to Psychology: The Frontiers of Psychological Inquiry

notes.note: Register for either lecture 1 or 2 (whichever has room). Both sections are the same.

A 4-credit option is offered for the Writing in the Majors component of this course OR if you take a discussion section in addition to the Tuesday/Thursday lectures. (A max of 4 credits is offered for this course.)
No prerequisties. May be used to satisfy the psychology major, breadth requirement and alternative prerequisite for biopsychology courses.
Recommended: introductory psychology or human development.

Enrollment limited to: junior or senior standing. Prerequisite: any one of the following Psych 2230, BIONB 2210 or BIONB 2220, or two majors-level biology courses plus psychology course.psychology course.
Prerequisites: Psych 3250 or HD 3700 (or taken concurrently), and permission of instructor. Students must commit to taking Psych 3280 in spring semester.

course.subject: PSYCH
course.course_title: Neuroethology: A Comparative Approach to Neural Circuits and Behavior

notes.note: Prerequisite: BIONB 2220, or equivalent with permission of instructor. Discussion will be held W 9:05-9:55 in W364 CMH.

Prerequisites: two majors-level biology courses or; biopsychology or neurobiology (e.g.,Psych 2230 or BIONB 2210, BIONB 2220); and an introductory course in perception, cognition, or language (e.g., Psych 1102, Psych 2090, Psych 2140, or Psych 2150).
Enrollment limited to: senior standing or permission of instructor.
Prerequisites: open to junior and senior psychology majors and to graduate students; open to others by permission.

course.subject: PSYCH
course.course_title: Effects of Aging on Sensory and Perceptual Systems

notes.note: Prerequisites: introductory course in biology or psychology, plus second course in perception, neuroscience, cognitive science, or biopsychology. Four credit option involves term paper or relevant web site. This course will be taught using the Socratic Method, in which the instructor asks questions-student responses will be made using Clickers, which will be used for responses to questions and ntr for attendance or grading.
Prerequisites: at least Psych 2230 or BIONB 2210. Recommended: additional course in biology, biopsychology, or neurobiology.
